Preconditions:
- The input array `balls` must not be null.
- The length of the input array `balls` must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 8.
- Each element in the input array `balls` must be greater than or equal to 1 and less than or equal to 6.
- The sum of all elements in the input array `balls` must be an even number.

Postconditions:
- The method should return a double value representing the probability that the two boxes have the same number of distinct balls.
- The returned probability value should be within 10^-5 of the actual value.